jvr_model.name: SCADA
jvr_model.description:
This is a generic configurable SCADA system dependency model. It has been developed based on the analysis of 36 mind maps produced by SCADA experts specializing in different aspects of SCADA.
This dependency model may be used as a template for producing systems specific models.

entity.name: Physical Security Personnel (guards etc.) are Ok
Design validation is detailed and accurate
All actions with data are Ok
Data of all types are Ok
External Dependencies (Environment) are recognized and dealt with appropriatly
System Life Cycle is Ok
entity.description: All stages of system development life cycle are managed effectively, and security and safety concernes are addressed at every stages

entity.name: System Architecture is Ok
entity.description: System Architecture functions reliably and as designed, and is available whenever required by authorized users

entity.name: Secure and safe operation of a SCADA system
entity.description: A SCADA systems is functional at all times, and operates safely and securely.

entity.name: Employees are Ok
entity.description: Employees have required education, training and certification, in order to be able to fulfill their responsibilities.

entity.name: Malicious operators are eliminated
entity.description: Required procedural activities are undertaken in order to identify potentially malicious operators (e.g. background check, regular personnel checks, behavior and personality observations)

entity.name: Manual supervision is Ok
entity.description: Operators are able to supervise system manually.

entity.name: Automatic supervision is Ok
entity.description: Operators are able to read and interpret the parameters of the system while it is automatically managed, and to identify situations when manual control is required
